FBIS3-50703 "drlat004_c_94008" FBIS-LAT-94-004 Document Type:Daily Report 6 Jan 1994 MEXICO Chiapas Crisis Rebels Reject Dialogue With Government PA0501153194 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1432 GMT 5 Jan 94 PA0501153194 Madrid EFE Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Tuxtla Gutierrez (Mexico), 5 Jan (EFE) -- The Mexican Government today asked the rebel Zapatista National Liberation Army (EZLN) to establish a dialogue and end the armed struggle, but the guerrillas have refused. Eloy Cantu Segovia, the sole spokesman for the Mexican Government in Chiapas, today reiterated the authorities' resolve to establish a dialogue on the condition that the rebels lay down their weapons. In response,the guerrillas sent a brief message to the local television station rejecting any type of negotiation with the government and announcing that the armed movement will continue.
